title: 2020 New York Red Bulls season
text:
The 2020 New York Red Bulls season was <a href="New%20York%20Red%20Bulls">the club's</a> twenty-fifth season in <a href="Major%20League%20Soccer">Major League Soccer</a>, the top division of <a href="soccer%20in%20the%20United%20States">soccer in the United States</a>.

Roster transactions.

Net income: $2,255,000
U.S. Open Cup.
New York Red Bulls will enter the 2020 U.S. Open Cup in the Round of 32.
Leagues Cup.
New York Red Bulls will enter the 2020 Leagues Cup in the Round of 16.
MLS is Back Tournament.
On June 10, MLS announced that a <a href="Bracket%20%28tournament%29">bracket</a> format named "MLS is Back Tournament" would begin July 8 at <a href="ESPN%20Wide%20World%20of%20Sports%20Complex">ESPN Wide World of Sports Complex</a> in <a href="Walt%20Disney%20World">Walt Disney World</a>, and end with the final on August 11.
